Function
--------
Function is a self contained block of statement.
Every function performs some specific task.

Functions can be classified as (Types of function) : 
    a. BuiltIn function | InBuilt Function | Standard Function | Library Function | Predefined function 

    Functions whose definition part is already defined.
    ex : printf(), scanf(), getch() etc 

    b. User defined function 

    Functions whose definition part is defined by the programmers or developers according to programming needs.

    ex: void display(){}, void show(){} etc

Advantages of function : 

    a. Function reduces program size.
    b. Function reduces redundancy of code.  
    c. Function makes debugging easier.
    d. Function reduces complexity of code.
    e. We can create n number of functions.
    f. Function can be called n number of times. 

Categories of function : 

    a. No argument no return type
    b. No argument with return type 
    c. With argument and no return type 
    d. With argument and with return type

Layout of using function :

#include<stdio.h>

    // function declaration 

int main(){

   // function calling  
    
   return 0; 
}

// function definition 

or 

#include<stdio.h>

   // function definition 

int main(){

   // function calling  
    
   return 0; 
}


